<br>
No &quot;break in&quot; as such.<br>
<br>
Bummer about the bard piece. I have a bracer from Fear, but, frankly, it's the piece I least needed. I wouldn't mind a Fear BP - lol.<br>
<br>
As said: For Fear, the break in is the biggest problem. <br>
<br>
The other key non-mezz related issue with Fear is that aggro has a different set of rules there - through away some of what you know about aggro. The key difference is that aggro chains between mobs. Let's say you aggro a mob, and then get away from it - due to pathing, outrunning it, whatever. That mob will proceed to path around the zone passing it's hate for you on to other mobs it comes across. They in turn will spread the wealth. Now, let's say that a healer tosses a heal on you - they now have half the zone hating them too. Oh, now someone starts buffing the both of you - guess what (yeah, I'm sure you got it)? This, BTW, leads to interesting encounters where you're doing whatever, and suddenly you find yourself death touched by one of the golems from half way across the zone.<br>
<br>
Now, it's not just during break in that aggro is a particular problem. There are a couple of mobs that will occasionally shadow step you to a random place in the zone - usually somewhere near the zone in, but not always. Folks have a nasty habit of running back to the raid party thinking about the mob that just did that to them, but ignoring the mobs they may pick up along the way. This is how many wipeouts after a seemingly successful break in happen.<br>
<br>
The reality is that you'll have a crowd of mobs around most of the time for the first long while after you zone into fear and start your first pulls. This is part of why mezz is key. There are also a few mobs that chain dispell there (eyes, terrors, and protoplasms in my experience). These you mezz even if you pull them single. Mezz them, snare them, fear them and keep them feared until dead. Otherwise, you'll burn through stacks and stacks of dots rebuffing (hate to see it when you watch Aego and Focus just disappear suddenly - 1500 HP  and a bunch of other benefits gone poof).<br>
<br>
Oh, and on the golems. One strategy I've seen that seems to help people remember not to break mezz: He/She who breaks mezz the most has to eat the death touch. For those that aren't aware, two of the golems have a death touch that they start off with (similar to Master Yael). First person to get aggro bites it automatic - done and over with. Can't recall the reset on it, but basically, you have the person eat the DT, then immediately pull and kill as fast as possible (before DT resets). Most of the Fear boss mobs are a 72 hour reset, so don't spare the mana. You'll have time to recharge before pulling the next major mob (usually there aren't many regular mobs left at this point).<br>
<br>
Last, but not least: Tell all your friends in other guilds that you're looking for a particular fear mob. It's not uncommon for a high guild to break fear and take just what they need. From the start of their break, you have 8 hours or so where you can have an easy ride of it. You may find that the mob you need is up with no one else in zone but a very manageable number of standard Fear mobs. It's also not a bad time to take folks in and go over how things work and what things look like for that time where you have to break Fear yourself. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub135.ezboard.com/fexodusfellowshipforumfrm6.showPrevMessage?topicID=1270.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub135.ezboard.com/fexodusfellowshipforumfrm6.showNextMessage?topicID=1270.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub135.ezboard.com/fexodusfellowshipforumfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1270.topic&index=10><img src=http://www.exodusfellowship.com/add-_reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub135.ezboard.com/fexodusfellowshipforumfrm6.emailToFriend?topicID=1270.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub135.ezboard.com/fexodusfellowshipforumfrm6.threadControl?topicID=1270.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/black_default/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub135.ezboard.com/fexodusfellowshipforumfrm6.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1270.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a h